**Verdict: yes, the D3D9 VS compile path can recompile on repeated cantina transitions.** The cache 
is not a process-lifetime shader-bytecode cache. It is owned by `Direct3d9_VertexShaderData`, which 
is owned by a refcounted `ShaderImplementationPassVertexShader`; when the last 
shader/effect/template/object reference goes away, the D3D vertex shaders are released and the next 
load recompiles.

Key trace:

- `ShaderImplementationPass` reads a `PVSH` filename and calls `VertexShader::fetch(buffer)` at [Shad
erImplementation.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/Shade
rImplementation.cpp:1354), also at the later version loaders around `1433`, `1511`, `1590`, `1670`, 
`1755`, `1841`.
- `ShaderImplementationPassVertexShader::fetch()` looks in global `ms_vertexShaderMap`; cache hit 
only increments refcount, miss constructs a new `VertexShader` at [ShaderImplementation.cpp](D:/Code/
swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderImplementation.cpp:2219).
- The constructor loads the `.vsh` text and creates `m_graphicsData = 
Graphics::createVertexShaderData(*this)` at [ShaderImplementation.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engi
ne/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderImplementation.cpp:2249) and [ShaderImplementation.
cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderImplementation.c
pp:2262).
- D3D9 implements that by allocating `new Direct3d9_VertexShaderData(vertexShader)` at [Direct3d9.cpp
](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9.cpp:3534).
- `Direct3d9_VertexShaderData` owns `m_nonPatchedVertexShader`, `m_container`, and the last-entry 
cache at [Direct3d9_VertexShaderData.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3
d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_VertexShaderData.cpp:322).
- Its destructor releases `m_nonPatchedVertexShader` and every `m_container` entry at [Direct3d9_Vert
exShaderData.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_V
ertexShaderData.cpp:407).
- `ShaderImplementationPassVertexShader::release()` deletes the vertex shader object at refcount 
zero, and the destructor removes it from `ms_vertexShaderMap` and deletes `m_graphicsData` at [Shader
Implementation.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderI
mplementation.cpp:2272) and [ShaderImplementation.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/librar
y/clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderImplementation.cpp:2293).

The compile gate is bounded only inside one live `Direct3d9_VertexShaderData`:

- Non-patched shaders compile once into `m_nonPatchedVertexShader` at [Direct3d9_VertexShaderData.cpp
](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_VertexShaderData.
cpp:663).
- Patched shaders compile once per `textureCoordinateSetKey` into `m_container` at [Direct3d9_VertexS
haderData.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_Vert
exShaderData.cpp:672).
- `m_lastRequestedKey/m_lastReturnedValue` is only a one-entry fast path, not ownership or eviction 
control, at [Direct3d9_VertexShaderData.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Dire
ct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_VertexShaderData.cpp:654).
- Actual D3DCompile is reached only through `createVertexShader()` at [Direct3d9_VertexShaderData.cpp
](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_VertexShaderData.
cpp:433), with `D3DCompile` inside the retained SEH guard at [Direct3d9_VertexShaderData.cpp](D:/Code
/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_VertexShaderData.cpp:119).

What evicts it:

- Shader templates are global-map cached only while refcounted. `ShaderTemplate::release()` removes 
from `ShaderTemplateList` and deletes at refcount zero: [ShaderTemplate.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/sr
c/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderTemplate.cpp:57).
- `StaticShaderTemplate::~StaticShaderTemplate()` releases its effect at [StaticShaderTemplate.cpp](D
:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/StaticShaderTemplate.cpp:134
).
- `ShaderEffect::~ShaderEffect()` releases its active implementation at [ShaderEffect.cpp](D:/Code/sw
g-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderEffect.cpp:49).
- `ShaderImplementation::~ShaderImplementation()` deletes passes, and pass destruction releases 
`m_vertexShader` at [ShaderImplementation.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/client
Graphics/src/shared/ShaderImplementation.cpp:142) and [ShaderImplementation.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v
2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderImplementation.cpp:978).
- Mesh/template runtime paths do release shaders/templates: `LocalShaderPrimitive` releases its 
shader at [ShaderPrimitiveSet.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src
/shared/ShaderPrimitiveSet.cpp:179), and primitive templates release shader templates at [ShaderPrimi
tiveSetTemplate.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/Shader
PrimitiveSetTemplate.cpp:724).

So the practical model is:

`cell object/appearance unload -> shader primitives/templates release -> 
StaticShaderTemplate/ShaderEffect/ShaderImplementation release -> 
ShaderImplementationPassVertexShader refcount may hit zero -> Direct3d9_VertexShaderData destroyed 
-> D3D shader cache gone -> next cantina load recompiles the same .vsh/key pairs.`

LOD change alone does not evict an already-live `Direct3d9_VertexShaderData`; it only increases the 
hit set if it causes a previously unloaded appearance/shader to be instantiated. The key is 
generated once when D3D9 static shader data is created from the static shader’s texture-coordinate 
map at [Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9
/src/win32/Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp:548), then cached as an `IDirect3DVertexShader9*` at [Direc
t3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Di
rect3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp:585).

I cannot give an exact cantina distinct-count from repo source alone because the cell’s concrete 
`.sht/.eft/.vsh` asset set lives in game data, not in this repo. But the realistic count is exactly:

`unique recreated (PVSH filename, textureCoordinateSetKey) pairs for objects whose last refs drop on 
the interior/exterior transition`.

That means Phase-32 is in the **recompile-thrash** bucket for unloadable cell assets. The fix angle 
should be a persistent compiled-bytecode cache keyed by `(vertex shader 
source/includes/defines/target, textureCoordinateSetKey)` or a longer-lived VS object cache, not 
assuming the existing `m_container` is enough.
